      <h1>How to Refinance Student Loans: Complete 2026 Guide</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">Americans collectively owe over $1.77 trillion in student loan debt, and millions of borrowers are paying interest rates far higher than what they could qualify for today. Student loan refinancing replaces one or more existing loans with a single new loan — ideally at a lower interest rate, shorter repayment term, or both. In the right circumstances, refinancing can save tens of thousands of dollars over the life of a loan. But the decision is not always straightforward, especially when federal loans are involved. This comprehensive guide walks you through everything you need to know about refinancing student loans in 2026, from eligibility requirements to a step-by-step application process.</p>
    </header>

